On the night of February 16th, 1929, Lucy Doheny, wife of Ned Doheny (son of the oil baron Edward L. Doheny) heard a gunshot in her home, The Greystone Mansion, at about 11:30 PM. She called the family doctor, and only when he arrived did she go investigate the noise. She and the doctor made their way to the source of the noise, where they discovered Hugh Plunkett, Ned's childhood friend, distraught, holding a gun. When Plunkett saw the two, he ran into Ned's room, and another gunshot was heard. Mrs. Doheny and the family doctor rushed in, to find both Ned and Plunkett dead on the ground. The official story in the papers the next day was that Plunkett let himself into the mansion (he had a key) had shot Ned, then himself. Case closed.
Or was it? #GreystoneMansionMurders #TrueCrime #Unsolved

I will be going over the symptoms, how to get a diagnosis, dealing with weight gain and trying to lose weight, diet plans for PCOS, and learning to manage and cope with your PCOS.

To get a diagnosis you must qualify using the Rotterdam criteria.

You must have 2/3 of the following symptoms:
 1. oligo/anovulation
2. hyperandrogenism
clinical (hirsutism or less commonly male pattern alopecia) or
biochemical (raised FAI or free testosterone)
3. polycystic ovaries on ultrasound

✉  Want to ask me for advice that I MAY answer in a video? Shoot me a question at Kendallsadvice[at]Gmail[dot]com


This is what Body Positivity means to me. For me, it is not a “get out of jail free card” to be able to skip working out and eating healthy. That is for my health both physical and mental. Working out provides me with so much stress relief. I ENJOY IT! I am not doing it because I’m punishing myself or to change. I eat healthy because it make me FEEL good. What I do NOT do is obsess over calories or a number on a scale. If I loose weight, then that’s great! But if not, that’s okay too and it will not change the way I feel about myself.After battling body image issues and an eating disorder, I decided I would never treat my body with disrespect again. That means not telling myself I’m not good enough or not deserving of happiness. My body is just my flesh vehicle, it doesn’t make me who I am.

In this video I discuss my experiences being cyber bullied in the past. Cyber bullying is so common and not a joke! Some people are more sensitive than others and it can truly hurt them. I was cyber bullied by my friends mom. It was strange being treated like that by an adult I knew and trusted. I remember feeling awful and I know that in combination with a lot of other things cause me to resort to an eating disorder. 

If you have ever cyber bullied someone please consider what it would be like to be in their shoes. If you have done in the past doesn't mean you can't change and start spreading positivity and love. You never know how you can affect someone's life.

"When a foreigner resides among you in your land, do not mistreat them. 34 The foreigner residing among you must be treated as your native-born. Love them as yourself, for you were foreigners in Egypt. I am the Lord your God.


Leviticus 25:44 says: "Your male and female slaves are to come from the nations around you; from them you may buy slaves.

Leviticus 24:16 says: "Whoever utters the name of the Lord must be put to death. The whole community must stone him, whether alien or native. If he utters the name, he must be put to death.

Leviticus 19:19 says: "'Do not wear clothing woven of two kinds of material." We'd like to give you a moment or two to check your labels.

Article about treating a burn- Note this article mentions to avoice makeup on your burn. I have read many others that say it's okay if its a 1st degree burn and has healed over a bit. I would suggest only wearing makeup when you need to and taking it off as soon as you are home from work/school/ect., but to each their own. I have burned my self several times and have never had an infection or scaring by applying concealer over it.  http://cincovidas.com/ouch-how-to-heal-a-curling-iron-burn-and-prevent-scarring/

In this video I show you how I cover burns when I accidentally burn my skin or face with a curling iron or straightener. This is a common mistake and even if you touch your skin for a second, it can leave a burn :( 

Make sure to cool the burn down with cold water, NOT ICE, and soothe with aloe vera. Treat the burn with healing oil or cream and protect it before any makeup touches it. then you can apply you concealer of the burn and cover your burn. I hope you find this video helpful! Enjoy.
